1
00:00:09,962 --> 00:00:12,959
Just like my photography teacher
used to say,

2
00:00:12,959 --> 00:00:15,732
“We can teach you processes,

3
00:00:15,732 --> 00:00:18,450
but we can’t teach you
how to see.”

4
00:00:18,450 --> 00:00:21,182
Either you have some capacity
to do that ….

5
00:00:21,182 --> 00:00:25,368
Then we'll say, spiritually,
the reason (a disciple)

6
00:00:25,368 --> 00:00:27,614
you make connection with the Guru

7
00:00:27,614 --> 00:00:30,540
is to get the eyes to see;

8
00:00:30,540 --> 00:00:34,062
to get to be initiated 
into subjective seeing.

9
00:00:34,154 --> 00:00:37,188
I’ll give you an example from
another one of my teachers,

10
00:00:37,188 --> 00:00:39,256
my biology teacher.

11
00:00:39,256 --> 00:00:42,160
He announced,
on the first day of class,

12
00:00:42,160 --> 00:00:45,143
you know the story? 
Anyway ….

13
00:00:46,062 --> 00:00:48,319
He announced 
on the first day of class, he said,

14
00:00:48,319 --> 00:00:52,720
“I’m going to teach you biology
in such a way

15
00:00:52,720 --> 00:00:55,617
as when you wake up in the morning
you’re going to see biology,

16
00:00:55,617 --> 00:00:57,893
when you brush your teeth
you’re going to see biology,

17
00:00:57,893 --> 00:01:01,299
when you eat your breakfast,
you’re going to see biology,

18
00:01:01,299 --> 00:01:04,966
when you go to the bathroom
you’re going to see biology.

19
00:01:04,967 --> 00:01:06,252
And he was right.

20
00:01:06,252 --> 00:01:11,681
When we started hearing from him
and his concepts,

21
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:17,430
our life was the same,
but there was this new awakening

22
00:01:17,430 --> 00:01:20,586
of seeing the biology
when you brushed your teeth,

23
00:01:20,586 --> 00:01:22,642
when you went to the bathroom,

24
00:01:22,642 --> 00:01:25,311
when you ate your breakfast. 

25
00:01:25,509 --> 00:01:30,687
Ṛṣi comes from 
the sanskrit word ‘dṛśi’,

26
00:01:30,687 --> 00:01:34,415
which means ‘to see’,
‘to observe’.

27
00:01:34,415 --> 00:01:42,291
So a real spiritual agent is an observer
of subjective reality.

28
00:01:43,507 --> 00:01:48,955
This is what a Guru is:
jñāninas tattva-darśinaḥ (Bg: 4.34);

29
00:01:48,986 --> 00:01:53,765
an observer of subjective reality.

30
00:01:53,811 --> 00:01:55,897
And as Śrīla Guru Mahārāj will say,

31
00:01:55,912 --> 00:01:58,623
and from that plane,
what they’ve observed

32
00:01:58,623 --> 00:02:02,403
is passing through 
their consciousness to you

33
00:02:02,403 --> 00:02:06,644
in the form of mantram
or revelation.

34
00:02:06,644 --> 00:02:10,824
Then putting yourself under the guidance 
of such an agent,

35
00:02:10,824 --> 00:02:15,178
you’re now in connection 
with revealed truth

36
00:02:15,178 --> 00:02:20,808
as opposed to objective truth;
objectively verifiable things

37
00:02:20,808 --> 00:02:24,155
which are just agreed upon.

38
00:02:24,155 --> 00:02:28,041
It’s a consensus of agreed upon 
norms of this world

39
00:02:28,041 --> 00:02:30,032
if we say ‘kilometres’ or ‘miles’.

40
00:02:30,524 --> 00:02:32,283
Spiritual agents.

41
00:02:32,283 --> 00:02:35,615
Prabhupād’s favorite expression:
‘transparent via medium’;

42
00:02:35,615 --> 00:02:39,937
they’re mediums, 
they’e curating a spiritual experience.

43
00:02:39,937 --> 00:02:43,981
So, what they’ve observed 
in the subjective world,

44
00:02:43,981 --> 00:02:45,731
they’re the agents
or the medium

45
00:02:45,731 --> 00:02:48,157
for expression of that
in the objective world. 

46
00:02:48,157 --> 00:02:56,050
So, depending upon their ‘locus standi’
or their GPS, where they're located

47
00:02:56,050 --> 00:03:00,867
in terms not only geographically, 
but historically,

48
00:03:00,867 --> 00:03:05,313
they’ll find the ways and means
amongst that population,

49
00:03:05,313 --> 00:03:06,930
where they're situated,

50
00:03:06,930 --> 00:03:10,711
to translate revealed truth 
into something

51
00:03:10,711 --> 00:03:13,871
that’s accessible to the local people.

52
00:03:13,952 --> 00:03:20,319
You may not need to understand, 
let’s say, art.

53
00:03:20,481 --> 00:03:25,403
They just keep seeing what they know 
is the real thing

54
00:03:25,404 --> 00:03:27,350
—the substantial, the higher stuff—

55
00:03:27,350 --> 00:03:29,465
keep exposing you to that,

56
00:03:29,465 --> 00:03:32,552
giving you some education
along the way,

57
00:03:32,552 --> 00:03:36,051
and the day will come 
where you’ll have an epiphany

58
00:03:36,051 --> 00:03:39,386
and what they see:
you’ll be seeing that.

59
00:03:39,386 --> 00:03:41,359
That's why the Vedas,
Guru Mahārāj said, it said,

60
00:03:41,359 --> 00:03:45,620
“It’s not as important to understand me.
Keep hearing.”

61
00:03:45,620 --> 00:03:47,378
Like we sing the songs every day,

62
00:03:47,378 --> 00:03:48,771
we hear certain ślokas every day 
over and over again;

63
00:03:48,771 --> 00:03:49,810
“Keep hearing”.

64
00:03:49,810 --> 00:03:52,008
We read Gītā over and over again

65
00:03:52,008 --> 00:03:55,187
and then at a certain time through ….

66
00:03:55,187 --> 00:03:58,238
And here, we add service.

67
00:03:58,238 --> 00:04:02,046
You can’t be antagonistic 
or envious of the teacher,

68
00:04:02,046 --> 00:04:06,492
or the agent, in the spiritual life.

69
00:04:06,492 --> 00:04:11,113
In the material world 
you might despise your teacher,

70
00:04:11,113 --> 00:04:13,938
and get the knowledge
or the information.

71
00:04:13,938 --> 00:04:15,946
Spiritually, that doesn’t work.

72
00:04:15,946 --> 00:04:19,103
Therefore: praṇipā—,
the respectful approach.

73
00:04:19,103 --> 00:04:22,260
Swāmi Avadhūt: Attitude.

74
00:04:22,260 --> 00:04:25,419
Sudhīr Goswāmī: And actually, really
it’s true materially, for the most part;

75
00:04:25,419 --> 00:04:27,848
when a child goes to school 
you tell them,

76
00:04:27,848 --> 00:04:30,472
“Put full faith in your teacher here.”

77
00:04:30,472 --> 00:04:31,774
And I know my own experience,

78
00:04:31,774 --> 00:04:36,026
the first nun I had—Sister Paul ….

79
00:04:36,026 --> 00:04:38,470
Sister Paul’s our teacher;

80
00:04:38,470 --> 00:04:41,404
we believe everything she says

81
00:04:41,404 --> 00:04:45,206
without hesitation, without doubt, 
without suspicion.

82
00:04:45,206 --> 00:04:49,345
So the transmission is very rapid

83
00:04:49,345 --> 00:04:52,658
because of that depth of belief.

84
00:04:52,658 --> 00:04:55,317
Then, went to another grade,
second and third grade,

85
00:04:55,317 --> 00:04:57,218
and Sister Paul wasn’t there,

86
00:04:57,218 --> 00:04:58,886
there was another sister.

87
00:04:58,886 --> 00:05:02,880
And at first I was upset,

88
00:05:03,203 --> 00:05:06,075
because I had 
so much faith in Sister Paul,

89
00:05:06,090 --> 00:05:09,869
I couldn’t understand
why she’s not teaching me.

90
00:05:09,869 --> 00:05:11,617
Where’s my first grade teacher?

91
00:05:11,617 --> 00:05:15,107
They said, “No-no, 
she’ll be teaching you here.”

92
00:05:15,107 --> 00:05:18,977
Then I learned to accept that teacher, 
give that faith.

93
00:05:18,977 --> 00:05:21,738
And this is the way of progress.

